## Web Research Complete

**Queries**: 3 web searches + 1 page fetch + local codebase analysis
**Sources**: 5 external sources + 4 local code files
**Artifact**: `/home/asiri/.archon/workspaces/alexsiri7/reli/artifacts/runs/f656ced173390d851aac8daf0976c969/web-research.md`

### Key Findings

- **Pattern**: Standard Tailwind underline-tab pattern uses `border-b-2 border-primary font-semibold` (active) and `border-b-2 border-transparent text-on-surface-variant` (inactive), with `-mb-px` on the nav to overlap the container's bottom border cleanly.
- **Best integration point**: Add the header bar inside `GraphView.tsx` — change the root div to `flex flex-col`, add a `<header>` with tabs on the left and the existing search bar (moved from `absolute` floating) on the right.
- **Token conflict**: Issue says `border-primary` (#c3c0ff, lavender) but the design file uses `#4F46E5` (= `primary-container`, indigo). Follow the issue spec (`border-primary`).
- **Height fix needed**: After adding the header, move `containerRef` to the inner canvas div (or subtract 48px from measured height) so `ForceGraph2D` receives the correct canvas dimensions.
- **Store wiring**: `GraphView.tsx` needs `const setMainView = useStore(s => s.setMainView)` — the "List" button calls `setMainView('list')`.

### Gaps

- `outline-variant` token is used in design HTML but not defined in `index.css` — may need a fallback class at runtime.

Sources:
- [Tailwind CSS Tabs — Tailwind UI](https://tailwindcss.com/plus/ui-blocks/application-ui/navigation/tabs)
- [Tailwind CSS Tabs — Flowbite](https://flowbite.com/docs/components/tabs/)
- [Active Tabs in Tailwind CSS — Tailkits](https://tailkits.com/blog/tailwind-active-tab/)
- [Animated Sliding Tabs — Sean C Davis](https://www.seancdavis.com/posts/animated-sliding-tabs-with-react-and-tailwind/)
- [Material Design 3 Tabs in Tailwind — Creative Tim](https://www.creative-tim.com/twcomponents/component/material-3-tabs)
